text.tspan: Share of SARS-CoV-2 sequences that are the delta variant
Shown is the delta variant's share of total analyzed sequences in the preceding two weeks.
Note: This share may not reflect the complete breakdown of cases, since only a fraction of all cases are
sequenced. Recently-discovered or actively-monitored variants may be overrepresented, as suspected
cases of these variants are likely to be sequenced preferentially or faster than other cases.
Data source: GISAID, via CoVariants.org – Last updated 23 April 2023
